-- Argentine Stocks: Grupo Galicia, Petrobras and Tenaris Gain
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-01-03T20:45:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-03/argentine-stocks-aluar-petroleo-brasileiro-and-tenaris-gain.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the close in Buenos
Aires.  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index rose 4.3 percent to 2,568.2. The market
was closed Dec. 30 and Jan. 2.  Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL)   surged 7.7 percent to
3.08 pesos, posting the steepest gain in 21 weeks. Argentina’s
largest consumer lender jumped today after the Instituto
Argentino de Mercado de Capitales, which calculates the Merval
index, said that Galicia would increase its weighting in the
benchmark to 23 percent from 13 percent.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)   rose 5.9 percent to 60.45
pesos, its largest increase since May 2010. Brazil’s state-
controlled oil company declared an oil and gas deposit in
Brazil’s Guara area commercially viable, according to a
statement sent yesterday to the country’s National Petroleum
Agency.  Tenaris SA (TEN)   increased 8.1 percent to 93.7 pesos for
the biggest gain in five weeks. The world’s largest producer of
seamless steel tubes used in the oil industry rose in line with
 oil prices  as manufacturing activity expanded in China and
India.  To contact the reporter on this story:
